# Auto commit & push

After completing a task that changes the repo, **commit and push without asking**.

## When to commit

- Feature fixes, data updates (`data/softcon-history.json`), scripts, UI changes — any intentional project change
- Skip commit only when: user explicitly says not to, question-only/review-only with no file edits, or changes contain secrets (`.env`, credentials)

## Workflow

1. Run `npm run build` when app code changed (skip for data-only JSON updates if build already verified)
2. `git status` + `git diff` — review what will ship; never commit secrets
3. Stage relevant files only
4. Commit with a concise message (why, not a file list). Use a HEREDOC-style message on Windows PowerShell here-strings if needed
5. `git push -u origin HEAD` (or `git push` if tracking exists)
6. Tell the user the commit hash briefly; mention if push failed

## Git safety (still required)

- Never `git config` changes, force-push to main, or `--no-verify` unless user asks
- Never amend unless user asks and amend rules are met
- Do not commit `.env` or credential files

## Deploy

This repo deploys via Vercel on push to `main`. Pushing is part of finishing the task.
